.TH "_read_hardreset" 9 "_read_hardreset" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
_read_hardreset \- read the HW reset line state of submodules contained in the hwmod module
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" _read_hardreset
.BI "(struct omap_hwmod *oh "  ","
.BI "const char *name "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "oh" 12
struct omap_hwmod *
.IP "name" 12
name of the reset line to look up and read
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Return the state of the reset line.  Returns -EINVAL if \fIoh\fP is
null, -ENOSYS if we have no way of reading the hardreset line
status on the currently-booted SoC, or passes along the return
value from \fB_lookup_hardreset\fP or the SoC's is_hardreset_asserted
code.
